getNextView

public final OWLObject getNextView()
Specified by:
getNextView in interface OWLObject
Returns:
If this object can be viewed as other object type(s) the next one is returned. Such views are lazily initialized, that is, whenever OWLObject.castTo(Class) was successful in casting to another object type this view instance is internally added (and only then it can be accessed by this method). Otherwise, this method returns this.

castTo

public final <T extends OWLObject> T castTo(java.lang.Class<T> javaClass)
Description copied from interface: OWLObject
OWLObjects can be casted to (viewed as) different implementation types. This method tries to cast this object into another OWL type, if possible. Whether this is possible depends on the axioms, assertions, and inferences in the OWL ontology or knowledge base this object is a member of.

If this instance has no model attached, it can only be viewed as a type it already has, see OWLObject.getNextView().

Specified by:
castTo in interface OWLObject
Parameters:
javaClass - The target OWL object type.
Returns:
This object casted to the target type.

canCastTo

public final boolean canCastTo(java.lang.Class<? extends OWLObject> javaClass)
Description copied from interface: OWLObject
Check if this object can be viewed as an instance of target type, that is, if it has already been viewed in this way, or if it has an attached model in which it has properties that permit it to be viewed in this way. If this method returns true, OWLObject.castTo(Class) on this instance should return an instance of target.

Specified by:
canCastTo in interface OWLObject
Parameters:
javaClass - The target type.
Returns:
true if this object can be viewed as an instance of the target type.

canCastToList

public final boolean canCastToList(ListVocabulary<? extends OWLValue> vocabulary)
Description copied from interface: OWLObject
This method is quite similar to OWLObject.canCastTo(Class) except that it checks if this OWL object can be viewed as a OWLList according to the given list vocabulary (which specifies the properties that need to be provided in order to be viewable as this kind of list).

Specified by:
canCastToList in interface OWLObject
Parameters:
vocabulary - The vocabulary supposed to be used by the target list.
Returns:
true if this object can be viewed as an instance of OWLList containing items that can contain items of the given class.

castToList

public final <T extends OWLValue> OWLList<T> castToList(ListVocabulary<T> vocabulary)
Description copied from interface: OWLObject
This method tries to cast this object into a OWLList, if possible. Whether this is possible depends on the axioms, assertions asserted about this OWL object and that will be matched again the given vocabulary.

Specified by:
castToList in interface OWLObject
Parameters:
vocabulary - The vocabulary supposed to be used by the target list.
Returns:
This object casted to OWLList and parameterized according to the list item class.
